Approach 2: Vercel AI SDK + Rich Text Editor (2–3 Days)
If you already have a custom React editor (TipTap, Lexical, Slate) and just want to add AI writing features to it, Vercel AI SDK is the modern standard. Handles streaming, model switching, and prompt engineering.
When to Choose This Approach

• You already have a custom React editor built

• You want control over prompts and model selection

• You’re comfortable with BYOK (bring your own key) for OpenAI/Anthropic API

• You have 2–3 days of engineering bandwidth
Step 1: Install Vercel AI SDK
bash
npm install ai @ai-sdk/openai @ai-sdk/anthropicStep 2: Set Up Environment Variables
bash
# .env.local
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...Step 3: Create a Streaming AI Endpoint
For Next.js 14/15 App Router:
typescript
// app/api/ai/route.ts
import { anthropic } from '@ai-sdk/anthropic';
import { openai } from '@ai-sdk/openai';
import { streamText } from 'ai';
export const maxDuration = 30;
export async function POST(req: Request) {
const { prompt, model = 'claude-sonnet-5', tone } = await req.json();
const systemPrompt = tone
? `You are a writing assistant. Rewrite text in a ${tone} tone.`
: 'You are a helpful writing assistant.';
const modelProvider = model.startsWith('gpt')
? openai(model)
: anthropic(model);
const result = streamText({
model: modelProvider,
system: systemPrompt,
prompt: prompt,
});
return result.toDataStreamResponse();
}Step 4: Wire Up AI Chat in Your Editor
For TipTap:
jsx
"use client";
import { useEditor, EditorContent } from '@tiptap/react';
import StarterKit from '@tiptap/starter-kit';
import { useState } from 'react';
import { useCompletion } from 'ai/react';
export default function AIEditor() {
const [showAIChat, setShowAIChat] = useState(false);
const editor = useEditor({
extensions: [StarterKit],
content: '<p>Start writing...</p>',
immediatelyRender: false,
});
const { completion, complete, isLoading } = useCompletion({
api: '/api/ai',
onFinish: (prompt, result) => {
editor?.commands.insertContent(result);
},
});
const handleAIChat = async (userPrompt: string) => {
await complete(userPrompt);
};
return (
<div className="border rounded-lg">
<MenuBar
editor={editor}
onAIChat={() => setShowAIChat(true)}
/>
<EditorContent editor={editor} className="p-4 min-h-64" />
{showAIChat && (
<AIChatPanel
onSubmit={handleAIChat}
onClose={() => setShowAIChat(false)}
streaming={completion}
isLoading={isLoading}
/>
)}
</div>
);
}Step 5: Build the AI Chat UI
